7/24/01 8:05:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Non-WIS Equip</span><hr size=1> Just a few comments on items...<br>
<br>
<hr border=0><i>Rings</i>: For jewel crafted rings, I like Velium Jade myself. They are 5ac +30hp +30mana. That extra 30 mana will do you a lot more good than the 1ac and 35hp you lose from Velium Fire Opal. I personally wear 2 of them.<br>
<hr border=0><i>Helms</i>: Crystal Chitin Circlet is, I believe, 24ac now, with +3wis. I know it has wis, but it's a nice helm. The problem with crystal chitin gear is that it is pretty pricey since the upgrade, as they are excellent items for quite a few classes. If you can handle negatives in "useless" stats (I can't, so i sold this crown), I'd recommend a Kobold Jester's Crown. 15ac +5agi +30cha -30int -5dex 0.0wt ALL/ALL. Doesn't have a texture. It's really quite a nice helm, I just personally don't like negative stats. Oh, and by useless, I mean stats which are of negligible benefit to the class, which in this case, is druid. =) One last one that is very nice (and yes it has wis too) is Square Helm. Looks like a steel plate helm, stats are 12ac +6wis +3agi.<br>
<hr border=0><i>Boots</i>: The ones suggested are nice. A few alternatives are any of the velious druid quest boots, or Vermiculated boots (if you have ability to do any of these).<br>
<hr border=0><i>Arms</i>: Again, the suggested ones above are nice. Another alternative is Giant Scalemail Arms. They do have wisdom on them, but are 11ac as well (I don't recall the other stats).<br>
<hr border=0><br>
Now I know several of my suggestions have wisdom on them, however, extra wisdom never hurt anyone. If you get enough extra wisdom, you could always replace *both* rings with Velium Jade. Probably the best, cheap, upgrade that gives good ac, hp, and mana. Extra wisdom over 200 is not a waist. The gain of mana from post-200 wisdom is just not anywhere near that of pre-200. Everything else that is affected by wisdom, still benefits from having post-200.<br>
<br>
Hope this information helps you out. If you have any more questions about equipment, feel free to ask, and I'd be glad to try to answer them the best I can... <p><center><a href="http://www.adamantine.org/"><img src="http://sandk1ng.homestead.com/files/kalsig54.jpg" border=0></a><BR><b>Kalethis Battlegar</b> <i>~</i> Level <b>55</b> Wood Elf Preserver (Druid) <i>of</i> Tunare<BR><b>Powah Rangah</b> <i>~</i> Level <b>22</b> Wood Elf Ranger <i>of</i> Tunare<BR>Guild <a href="http://www.adamantine.org/"><b>Adamantine Kinship</b></a> on <i>Mithaniel Marr</i><BR><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=64984"><i>Character profile at Castersrealm</i></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uneroeseq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NeroesEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/25/01 1:24:18 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.kvikhandel.dk/waypoint/wolf.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Non-WIS Equip</span><hr size=1> I recently had to do the same. (Replace Wis with some other items)<br>
